==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc}} {{term|μωρός|lang=grc||foolish|tr=moros}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/mɔrɒn/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{obsolete}} A person of borderline intelligence in the former classification of mental retardation, having of an intelligence quotient of 50-69.
# {{informal}} A person who makes [[uncool]], [[unfunny]], [[uninteresting]], or [[irrelevant]] (see [[lame]]) attempts to impress others and draw attention to himself, especially in a flawed attempt to act like someone else.
# {{slang}} An [[idiot]].

====Usage notes====
Though originally a psychological, clinical, and medical term, it is currently used as a pejorative term against someone perceived as stupid. Current term for having an IQ between 50 and 69 is [[mild]] [[mental]] [[retardation]].

